Setting.Name: Number of partitions for k-fold test

Comment.Text:
Use this scenario on your own risk.
This scenario can be used to initialize a classifier based on the predictions recorded in the file. Training is triggered by the number 199 which is send by the stimulator every 10 trials/symbols. So this scenario will only train on the first 10 trials no matter how much data you recorded (probably only the first 9 trials as there is an issue with the execution order of the boxes, the xdawn begins training before epoch labeling processed the last trial). Thus, make sure you run this script on data you recorded in free mode (free mode and without any letters in the WordToSpell field of the python frontend) and with enough repititions (e.g. 20)
The predictions should start from 1 if they start from zero it will not work (so only newly recorded files which record the predictions starting from 1 will work with this)
